WILD MOUNTAINS
Through valleys green and peaks so high,
The mountains cradle clouds like dreams.
In wildness fierce, beneath the sky,
Nature's spirit, ever gleams.
Within their majesty, I see,
The heart of earth, forever free.



- Marie Under
